Class SimpleFeatureOutputReducer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Reducer<GeoWaveInputKey,org.apache.hadoop.io.ObjectWritable,GeoWaveInputKey,org.apache.hadoop.io.ObjectWritable>
      • mil.nga.giat.geowave.accumulo.mapreduce.GeoWaveReducer
        • mil.nga.giat.geowave.analytics.clustering.mapreduce.SimpleFeatureOutputReducer

  • public class SimpleFeatureOutputReducer
extends GeoWaveReducer
    Remove duplicate input objects and write out as a simple feature with geometry projected onto CRS EPSG:4326. The output feature contains the ID of the originating object. The intent is to create a light weight uniform object that reuses GeoWave data formats to feed analytic processes. If the input object does not require adjustment after de-duplication, use mil.nga.giat.geowave.accumulo.mapreduce.dedupe.GeoWaveDedupReducer OutputFeature Attributes, see AnalyticFeature.ClusterFeatureAttribute Context configuration parameters include:
